Text.LocalizedString: I haven’t seen you around here before.//Are you new?

Text.LocalizedString: Hopefully, we’ll all eventually remember, and bringing your own bag will be the new normal.//<portrait=happy>Ah, I see you have a backpack! You’ve got the idea, <PlayerName>$player</>.

Text.SourceString: Seems like Dad’s been complaining about the recycling area more lately.//I don’t go to that part of the island, so I have no idea what’s going on with it.
Text.LocalizedString: Seems like Dad’s been complaining about the recycling area more lately.//I don’t go to that part of the island, so I have no idea what’s going on with it.

Text.SourceString: But I don’t think it’s that bad.//Everybody takes care of it, and it looks pretty clean from a distance.//<portrait=sad>But what do I know?
Text.LocalizedString: But I don’t think it’s that bad.//Everybody takes care of it, and it looks pretty clean from a distance.//<portrait=sad>But what do I know?

Text.SourceString: I thought of turning my bonsai garden into a small fruit garden, but the only fruit I like is mangoes.
Text.LocalizedString: I thought of turning my bonsai garden into a small fruit garden, but the only fruit I like is mangoes.

Text.SourceString: I suppose I could plant mango trees.//<portrait=sad>Hmm. It’d be a boring fruit garden with only one kind of tree, though.
Text.LocalizedString: I suppose I could plant mango trees.//<portrait=sad>Hmm. It’d be a boring fruit garden with only one kind of tree, though.

Text.SourceString: It might not be a bad idea to plant more banana trees. <NPCName>Sam</>’s never seems to have enough.//<portrait=annoyed>Bananas, not trees.
Text.LocalizedString: It might not be a bad idea to plant more banana trees. <NPCName>Sam</>’s never seems to have enough.//<portrait=annoyed>Bananas, not trees.

Text.SourceString: Of course. I’ll plant fruit trees when I have a bigger garden. Don’t you worry!
Text.LocalizedString: Of course. I’ll plant fruit trees when I have a bigger garden. Don’t you worry!

Text.SourceString: When I move out, I’ll look for a place with a yard so I can bring my bonsai.
Text.LocalizedString: When I move out, I’ll look for a place with a yard so I can bring my bonsai.

Text.SourceString: Who knows, I might start planting one or two things. I always thought it would be so fun to have a pumpkin patch in Fall.
Text.LocalizedString: Who knows, I might start planting one or two things. I always thought it would be so fun to have a pumpkin patch in Fall.

Text.SourceString: I have a lot of work to catch up on.
Text.LocalizedString: I have a lot of work to catch up on.

Text.SourceString: As far as I know, fig and juniper are the two most common bonsai trees.//<portrait=sad>Errr…
Text.LocalizedString: As far as I know, fig and juniper are the two most common bonsai trees.//<portrait=sad>Errr…

Text.SourceString: I’m not a bonsai expert, so don’t quote me on that.//<portrait=sad>I was just trying to make conversation.//But I’m pretty sure.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not a bonsai expert, so don’t quote me on that.//<portrait=sad>I was just trying to make conversation.//But I’m pretty sure.

Text.SourceString: Errr, you are literally in my way.
Text.LocalizedString: Errr, you are literally in my way.

Text.SourceString: I’m not sure why you’re here, to be honest.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not sure why you’re here, to be honest.

Text.SourceString: My one piece of advice about bonsai is don’t water them every day.//I’d find out the needs of each individual tree and then make sure to provide that.//That’s the safest way to do it.
Text.LocalizedString: My one piece of advice about bonsai is don’t water them every day.//I’d find out the needs of each individual tree and then make sure to provide that.//That’s the safest way to do it.

Text.SourceString: Sorry if that’s boring. I just thought since you’re a farmer, you’d be into that kind of stuff.//And I’m generalizing now. Oh gosh. I’m sorry.
Text.LocalizedString: Sorry if that’s boring. I just thought since you’re a farmer, you’d be into that kind of stuff.//And I’m generalizing now. Oh gosh. I’m sorry.

Text.SourceString: Umm?
Text.LocalizedString: Umm?

Text.SourceString: Umm, what?
Text.LocalizedString: Umm, what?

Text.SourceString: There isn’t much nightlife around here, like nightclubs or late-night karaoke bars.
Text.LocalizedString: There isn’t much nightlife around here, like nightclubs or late-night karaoke bars.

Text.SourceString: Are you surprised?//<portrait=concerned>You probably knew that before moving here, didn’t you?
Text.LocalizedString: Are you surprised?//<portrait=concerned>You probably knew that before moving here, didn’t you?

Text.SourceString: Sure, I like my job. I don’t have to see too many people.//<portrait=annoyed>That would be exhausting.
Text.LocalizedString: Sure, I like my job. I don’t have to see too many people.//<portrait=annoyed>That would be exhausting.

Text.SourceString: Hmm. One thing about my brother, <NPCName>Theo</>, is he’s very artistic, just like Mom.//He sings and plays instruments.
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm. One thing about my brother, <NPCName>Theo</>, is he’s very artistic, just like Mom.//He sings and plays instruments.

Text.SourceString: Not me. I don’t sing or play anything.
Text.LocalizedString: Not me. I don’t sing or play anything.

Text.SourceString: I like to walk outside by myself when I’m stuck on something.//Work stuff, usually.
Text.LocalizedString: I like to walk outside by myself when I’m stuck on something.//Work stuff, usually.

Text.SourceString: I don’t go too far from the house, though.//Usually, just to the lake and back.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t go too far from the house, though.//Usually, just to the lake and back.

Text.SourceString: If I had to choose a favorite place, I’d say the library.//People usually leave you alone in there.
Text.LocalizedString: If I had to choose a favorite place, I’d say the library.//People usually leave you alone in there.

Text.SourceString: Plus, it’s quiet.
Text.LocalizedString: Plus, it’s quiet.

Text.SourceString: I try to eat one fruit a day, every day. I like to be consistent.
Text.LocalizedString: I try to eat one fruit a day, every day. I like to be consistent.

Text.SourceString: Today? Hmm. I had a banana this morning.
Text.LocalizedString: Today? Hmm. I had a banana this morning.

Text.SourceString: I try to eat one fruit a day, every day. I like to be consistent.
Text.LocalizedString: I try to eat one fruit a day, every day. I like to be consistent.

Text.SourceString: Today? Hmm. I ate a tomato this morning. Yeah, that’s a fruit!
Text.LocalizedString: Today? Hmm. I ate a tomato this morning. Yeah, that’s a fruit!

Text.SourceString: I try to eat one fruit a day, every day. I like to be consistent.
Text.LocalizedString: I try to eat one fruit a day, every day. I like to be consistent.

Text.SourceString: Today? Hmm. I had an artichoke today.
Text.LocalizedString: Today? Hmm. I had an artichoke today.

Text.SourceString: Kidding. I had some grapes.//<portrait=concerned>Why are you so interested in my diet, anyway?
Text.LocalizedString: Kidding. I had some grapes.//<portrait=concerned>Why are you so interested in my diet, anyway?

Text.SourceString: I try to eat one fruit a day, every day. I like to be consistent.
Text.LocalizedString: I try to eat one fruit a day, every day. I like to be consistent.

Text.SourceString: We had some leftover grapes from Fall. So I just had some of those this morning.
Text.LocalizedString: We had some leftover grapes from Fall. So I just had some of those this morning.

Text.SourceString: Breakfast food? I like pancakes.//<portrait=sad>Umm…
Text.LocalizedString: Breakfast food? I like pancakes.//<portrait=sad>Umm…

Text.SourceString: So, you seem to like wearing boots, huh?
Text.LocalizedString: So, you seem to like wearing boots, huh?

Text.SourceString: Errr, never mind my poor attempt at conversation.//I feel awkward now.
Text.LocalizedString: Errr, never mind my poor attempt at conversation.//I feel awkward now.

Text.SourceString: I repot my bonsai every three to five years, but I think every four years is fine.//Keep in mind some faster-growing trees need to be repotted more often.
Text.LocalizedString: I repot my bonsai every three to five years, but I think every four years is fine.//Keep in mind some faster-growing trees need to be repotted more often.

Text.SourceString: Repotting is easy if you have the right tool.//For bonsai, you need a special root rake.//<portrait=sad>Umm, yeah.
Text.LocalizedString: Repotting is easy if you have the right tool.//For bonsai, you need a special root rake.//<portrait=sad>Umm, yeah.

Text.SourceString: Hey…
Text.LocalizedString: Hey…

Text.SourceString: I was offered an on-site position at my job, but I declined.//It could be a new experience, living in a big city.//Finally be on my own, get a pet maybe?
Text.LocalizedString: I was offered an on-site position at my job, but I declined.//It could be a new experience, living in a big city.//Finally be on my own, get a pet maybe?

Text.SourceString: But no. I really don’t want to leave Coral Island unless I have to.//I can always travel if I want to get away for a little while.
Text.LocalizedString: But no. I really don’t want to leave Coral Island unless I have to.//I can always travel if I want to get away for a little while.

Text.SourceString: I wonder if there’s a bonsai version of that tree by your farm.
Text.LocalizedString: I wonder if there’s a bonsai version of that tree by your farm.

Text.SourceString: The tree on the lookout, the one by the lighthouse? Doesn’t ring a bell?
Text.LocalizedString: The tree on the lookout, the one by the lighthouse? Doesn’t ring a bell?

Text.SourceString: I was on my way to the beach yesterday and ran into <NPCName>Dippa</>. I said hi, but they ignored me.
Text.LocalizedString: I was on my way to the beach yesterday and ran into <NPCName>Dippa</>. I said hi, but they ignored me.

Text.SourceString: It’s been on my mind. I keep wondering if I did anything wrong.//Or they could have just been having a bad day, I guess. Hmm.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s been on my mind. I keep wondering if I did anything wrong.//Or they could have just been having a bad day, I guess. Hmm.

Text.SourceString: I don’t feel like talking right now.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t feel like talking right now.

Text.SourceString: Working from home is nice because you can save money on commuting and put it in the bank instead.
Text.LocalizedString: Working from home is nice because you can save money on commuting and put it in the bank instead.

Text.SourceString: My dad is nice enough to let me stay here rent-free.
Text.LocalizedString: My dad is nice enough to let me stay here rent-free.

Text.SourceString: I usually stay at my friend’s villa on Mondays.//When she isn’t in town, that is.
Text.LocalizedString: I usually stay at my friend’s villa on Mondays.//When she isn’t in town, that is.

Text.SourceString: You know, just to keep an eye on it.
Text.LocalizedString: You know, just to keep an eye on it.

Text.SourceString: Don’t tell anybody, but I think somebody else lives in that villa at the beach.//I have my suspicions.
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t tell anybody, but I think somebody else lives in that villa at the beach.//I have my suspicions.

Text.SourceString: I work remotely from home. So, I don’t need to go out very often, which is perfect for me.
Text.LocalizedString: I work remotely from home. So, I don’t need to go out very often, which is perfect for me.

Text.SourceString: I guess I’m not the talkative type.
Text.LocalizedString: I guess I’m not the talkative type.

Text.SourceString: It’s hard for me to make small talk.//And it’s especially hard if the small talk needs to be non–bonsai related.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s hard for me to make small talk.//And it’s especially hard if the small talk needs to be non–bonsai related.

Text.SourceString: Living in a cabin in the middle of nowhere sounds great.
Text.LocalizedString: Living in a cabin in the middle of nowhere sounds great.

Text.SourceString: I don’t know why it never occurred to me to become a farmer like you.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t know why it never occurred to me to become a farmer like you.

Text.SourceString: Umm…
Text.LocalizedString: Umm…

Text.SourceString: The library is nice and quiet.//You can read in peace for hours without anybody bothering you.
Text.LocalizedString: The library is nice and quiet.//You can read in peace for hours without anybody bothering you.

Text.SourceString: I need that kind of space in my life.
Text.LocalizedString: I need that kind of space in my life.

Text.SourceString: I like reading about bonsai and cacti in my spare time.
Text.LocalizedString: I like reading about bonsai and cacti in my spare time.

Text.SourceString: Umm, what do you want?
Text.LocalizedString: Umm, what do you want?

Text.SourceString: Hmm. People say I come across as off-putting sometimes.
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm. People say I come across as off-putting sometimes.

Text.SourceString: I promise you, I’m not. I just don’t have anything to talk about.//<portrait=normal>Also, the things I could talk about for hours, I legally can’t discuss with anyone outside my team. So…
Text.LocalizedString: I promise you, I’m not. I just don’t have anything to talk about.//<portrait=normal>Also, the things I could talk about for hours, I legally can’t discuss with anyone outside my team. So…

Text.SourceString: I like living at home with Dad and <NPCName>Theo</>.//<portrait=normal>I just hope they don’t feel like I’m a burden or anything. Ha ha ha.
Text.LocalizedString: I like living at home with Dad and <NPCName>Theo</>.//<portrait=normal>I just hope they don’t feel like I’m a burden or anything. Ha ha ha.

Text.SourceString: Hmm…
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm…

Text.SourceString: Socket & Pan is a good store, but they can’t build computers yet.
Text.LocalizedString: Socket & Pan is a good store, but they can’t build computers yet.

Text.SourceString: I built my PC in Pokyo. I had to wait months for some parts ’cause there was a shortage.//It was worth it, though. Now when I play Resident Vile, my PC isn’t angry anymore. And the graphics look amazing.
Text.LocalizedString: I built my PC in Pokyo. I had to wait months for some parts ’cause there was a shortage.//It was worth it, though. Now when I play Resident Vile, my PC isn’t angry anymore. And the graphics look amazing.

Text.SourceString: I need to get this done before noon.
Text.LocalizedString: I need to get this done before noon.

Text.SourceString: Don’t you have animals to tend to?
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t you have animals to tend to?

Text.SourceString: There are so many games. It makes it hard to leave my room. That’s where I work. And game, I guess.//Do you play? I haven’t beaten all the games in the Resident Vile series, but I’m taking my time. Just enjoying the story.
Text.LocalizedString: There are so many games. It makes it hard to leave my room. That’s where I work. And game, I guess.//Do you play? I haven’t beaten all the games in the Resident Vile series, but I’m taking my time. Just enjoying the story.

Text.SourceString: I also like retro games. Not old ones, but the ones with a nostalgic feeling.//My favorite genre has to be farming simulators. Can’t get enough of them. I might make one someday!
Text.LocalizedString: I also like retro games. Not old ones, but the ones with a nostalgic feeling.//My favorite genre has to be farming simulators. Can’t get enough of them. I might make one someday!

Text.SourceString: You should only water bonsai trees when the soil gets slightly dry, to avoid overwatering them.
Text.LocalizedString: You should only water bonsai trees when the soil gets slightly dry, to avoid overwatering them.

Text.SourceString: Ah, am I talking about bonsai again?//We can talk about the weather if you want.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, am I talking about bonsai again?//We can talk about the weather if you want.

Text.SourceString: I went to Pokyo several times for team meetings. Once, somebody told me to get a massage so I could relax.
Text.LocalizedString: I went to Pokyo several times for team meetings. Once, somebody told me to get a massage so I could relax.

Text.SourceString: That was rude.//It made me mad, and I wasn’t relaxed at all.
Text.LocalizedString: That was rude.//It made me mad, and I wasn’t relaxed at all.

Text.SourceString: I work in security for a Pokyo-based company.//Cyber security. Why are you asking?
Text.LocalizedString: I work in security for a Pokyo-based company.//Cyber security. Why are you asking?

Text.SourceString: Sorry, I can’t talk too much about my job.//My employer is very strict about it.
Text.LocalizedString: Sorry, I can’t talk too much about my job.//My employer is very strict about it.

Text.SourceString: Game development isn’t as easy as it sounds. It’s much more fun than I thought it would be, though!
Text.LocalizedString: Game development isn’t as easy as it sounds. It’s much more fun than I thought it would be, though!

Text.SourceString: Uh-huh, I make games in my free time. I’ve made a couple of games, not a lot.
Text.LocalizedString: Uh-huh, I make games in my free time. I’ve made a couple of games, not a lot.

Text.SourceString: It’s amazing how wealthy some people are. I’ve been doing my job for a while, and I’m still not used to it.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s amazing how wealthy some people are. I’ve been doing my job for a while, and I’m still not used to it.

Text.SourceString: I’ve said too much.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve said too much.

Text.SourceString: Oh, I just cracked my back! That felt good.//<portrait=concerned>I think I’ve been sitting down too long. I pulled an all-nighter last night until 4 am, doing QA for my game.//So many bugs.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, I just cracked my back! That felt good.//<portrait=concerned>I think I’ve been sitting down too long. I pulled an all-nighter last night until 4 am, doing QA for my game.//So many bugs.

Text.SourceString: I prefer not to work on the weekend, but sometimes I have no choice.
Text.LocalizedString: I prefer not to work on the weekend, but sometimes I have no choice.

Text.SourceString: I’ve been wanting to upgrade my PC, but gosh. The parts are so expensive.//Too much demand right now. It’s gonna have to wait.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve been wanting to upgrade my PC, but gosh. The parts are so expensive.//Too much demand right now. It’s gonna have to wait.

Text.SourceString: It’s always nerve-racking to post my game updates.//I don’t know. I’m scared to look at the comments, I guess.//I’m scared people might hate it. Or hate <Italic>me</> for it. I don’t know.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s always nerve-racking to post my game updates.//I don’t know. I’m scared to look at the comments, I guess.//I’m scared people might hate it. Or hate <Italic>me</> for it. I don’t know.

Text.SourceString: I know this is such a cliché, but I just love how full of life Spring is. It’s so nice to listen to the birds again.//Birds are cool. Yeah.
Text.LocalizedString: I know this is such a cliché, but I just love how full of life Spring is. It’s so nice to listen to the birds again.//Birds are cool. Yeah.

Text.SourceString: It might be just my imagination, but my bonsai look so happy today. Like they’re glad Winter is finally over.
Text.LocalizedString: It might be just my imagination, but my bonsai look so happy today. Like they’re glad Winter is finally over.

Text.SourceString: Do you know how to make a Spring frittata? I think you need an egg and some vegetables. Hmm.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you know how to make a Spring frittata? I think you need an egg and some vegetables. Hmm.

Text.SourceString: Spring makes me crave Spring frittatas.
Text.LocalizedString: Spring makes me crave Spring frittatas.

Text.SourceString: I’ll work tonight. I wanna enjoy Spring today.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ll work tonight. I wanna enjoy Spring today.

Text.SourceString: I love seeing all the plants come back to life in the Spring.
Text.LocalizedString: I love seeing all the plants come back to life in the Spring.

Text.SourceString: I’m gonna miss Spring.//<portrait=annoyed>I’m not looking forward to the hot Summer.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m gonna miss Spring.//<portrait=annoyed>I’m not looking forward to the hot Summer.

Text.SourceString: I saw a crab playing around in the garden this morning. I don’t know how it got there, ’cause we’re pretty far from the beach.
Text.LocalizedString: I saw a crab playing around in the garden this morning. I don’t know how it got there, ’cause we’re pretty far from the beach.

Text.SourceString: I wanna spend my Summer napping indoors all day. Hmm.//Maybe I <Italic>should</> do that.
Text.LocalizedString: I wanna spend my Summer napping indoors all day. Hmm.//Maybe I <Italic>should</> do that.

Text.SourceString: My PC’s fan was angry yesterday. <Italic>Mmm, mmm, mmm</> all day long.//The heat got to it too, I think.
Text.LocalizedString: My PC’s fan was angry yesterday. <Italic>Mmm, mmm, mmm</> all day long.//The heat got to it too, I think.

Text.SourceString: We planted some lemongrass in the garden. It repels mosquitoes.//Well, not <Italic>we</>, actually. Mom did. She planted when–//Anyway, lemongrass really helps with the Summer bug situation.
Text.LocalizedString: We planted some lemongrass in the garden. It repels mosquitoes.//Well, not <Italic>we</>, actually. Mom did. She planted when–//Anyway, lemongrass really helps with the Summer bug situation.

Text.SourceString: Fall in our house is a bummer.//It wasn’t always like that. We used to make our own mooncakes. They weren’t as good as the ones from the Harvest Festival.//But making them was. It was cool.
Text.LocalizedString: Fall in our house is a bummer.//It wasn’t always like that. We used to make our own mooncakes. They weren’t as good as the ones from the Harvest Festival.//But making them was. It was cool.

Text.SourceString: There’s a corn maze at the harvest festival in a nearby town.//Yeah, went there a couple of times. It was kinda fun.//It’s fun here too. I like the pumpkin-smashing game.
Text.LocalizedString: There’s a corn maze at the harvest festival in a nearby town.//Yeah, went there a couple of times. It was kinda fun.//It’s fun here too. I like the pumpkin-smashing game.

Text.SourceString: A few Falls ago, I volunteered to read scary stories at the school.//Never got invited back. I don’t really think they enjoyed it.
Text.LocalizedString: A few Falls ago, I volunteered to read scary stories at the school.//Never got invited back. I don’t really think they enjoyed it.

Text.SourceString: The cooler weather is nice.//It’s my favorite.
Text.LocalizedString: The cooler weather is nice.//It’s my favorite.

Text.SourceString: I think I’ll watch some old classics tonight after work. Like <Italic>Alakazam</> or <Italic>Shriek</>.
Text.LocalizedString: I think I’ll watch some old classics tonight after work. Like <Italic>Alakazam</> or <Italic>Shriek</>.

Text.SourceString: The Fall vibe is perfect for watching witchy horror films.
Text.LocalizedString: The Fall vibe is perfect for watching witchy horror films.

Text.SourceString: All my bonsai are temperate, so I don’t have to do too much to prepare them for Winter.//<portrait=concerned>Well, it’s still a lot of work, actually, but at least it’s not as much as for tropical bonsai.
Text.LocalizedString: All my bonsai are temperate, so I don’t have to do too much to prepare them for Winter.//<portrait=concerned>Well, it’s still a lot of work, actually, but at least it’s not as much as for tropical bonsai.

Text.SourceString: It’s kinda nice not to have to work outdoors in this weather.//And my PC has angry fans, which is great for keeping me warm.//Oh, not always. Only when I run certain programs.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s kinda nice not to have to work outdoors in this weather.//And my PC has angry fans, which is great for keeping me warm.//Oh, not always. Only when I run certain programs.

Text.SourceString: A cat broke into our home one night last Winter. It broke the window in the kitchen, stole some food, and left.//We woke up to a freezing cold kitchen. It took us all day to fix the window.//Oh, it was a cat, all right. There were hairs!
Text.LocalizedString: A cat broke into our home one night last Winter. It broke the window in the kitchen, stole some food, and left.//We woke up to a freezing cold kitchen. It took us all day to fix the window.//Oh, it was a cat, all right. There were hairs!

Text.SourceString: I heard there’ll be a lot of interesting booths at the Winter Fair.//I wonder if it’s worth going when it’s this cold.
Text.LocalizedString: I heard there’ll be a lot of interesting booths at the Winter Fair.//I wonder if it’s worth going when it’s this cold.

Text.SourceString: I think I’ll work on my game this Winter. More than usual.
Text.LocalizedString: I think I’ll work on my game this Winter. More than usual.

Text.SourceString: Hmm. Do I want to make games full time? I don’t know. That sounds scary.//What if they don’t sell? I need a stable income.
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm. Do I want to make games full time? I don’t know. That sounds scary.//What if they don’t sell? I need a stable income.

Text.SourceString: The one good thing about Winter is I can wear hoodies every day, and no one judges me.
Text.LocalizedString: The one good thing about Winter is I can wear hoodies every day, and no one judges me.

Text.SourceString: Pufferfish is an oil-drilling company.//From what I gather, they’re looking to install rigs offshore.
Text.LocalizedString: Pufferfish is an oil-drilling company.//From what I gather, they’re looking to install rigs offshore.

Text.SourceString: They’re legally prevented from doing it until they get a majority vote on this island.
Text.LocalizedString: They’re legally prevented from doing it until they get a majority vote on this island.

Text.SourceString: Pufferfish is moving its office here to buy property.//I hope nobody’s selling. I’d hate to see Coral Island become an oil-drilling spot.
Text.LocalizedString: Pufferfish is moving its office here to buy property.//I hope nobody’s selling. I’d hate to see Coral Island become an oil-drilling spot.

Text.SourceString: I’m bringing coconut drinks to the Cherry Blossom Festival tomorrow.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m bringing coconut drinks to the Cherry Blossom Festival tomorrow.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Theo</> gets a stomachache every time he drinks milk. He hates it.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Theo</> gets a stomachache every time he drinks milk. He hates it.

Text.SourceString: Yet he still eats cheese. Silly man.
Text.LocalizedString: Yet he still eats cheese. Silly man.

Text.SourceString: Have you gotten anything from Socket & Pan yet?//They have good products.
Text.LocalizedString: Have you gotten anything from Socket & Pan yet?//They have good products.

Text.SourceString: Buy your Summer seeds yet, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Buy your Summer seeds yet, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: I don’t stay at the villa during Summer, because <NpcName>Nina</> is already here.//Besides, the beach gets really hot <Italic>really</> early in the morning anyway.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t stay at the villa during Summer, because <NpcName>Nina</> is already here.//Besides, the beach gets really hot <Italic>really</> early in the morning anyway.

Text.SourceString: It’s too hot to use a blanket at night now.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s too hot to use a blanket at night now.

Text.SourceString: It’s a problem, because I sleep better with one.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s a problem, because I sleep better with one.

Text.SourceString: My mom was a high-spirited person. That’s why I’m so lively.
Text.LocalizedString: My mom was a high-spirited person. That’s why I’m so lively.

Text.SourceString: Kidding…
Text.LocalizedString: Kidding…

Text.SourceString: Are you attending the beach cleanup tomorrow?
Text.LocalizedString: Are you attending the beach cleanup tomorrow?

Text.SourceString: Me too. See you there.
Text.LocalizedString: Me too. See you there.

Text.SourceString: Well, I hope to see you there.
Text.LocalizedString: Well, I hope to see you there.

Text.SourceString: It’s my dad’s birthday today, so I’m making seafood ramen for dinner.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s my dad’s birthday today, so I’m making seafood ramen for dinner.

Text.SourceString: It’s his favorite.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s his favorite.

Text.SourceString: I really don’t feel like chatting today, <PlayerName>$player</>. I hope you understand.
Text.LocalizedString: I really don’t feel like chatting today, <PlayerName>$player</>. I hope you understand.

Text.SourceString: I’m so sorry, <PlayerName>$player</>. I really can’t talk right now.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m so sorry, <PlayerName>$player</>. I really can’t talk right now.

Text.SourceString: My hoodie comes in handy in this weather.
Text.LocalizedString: My hoodie comes in handy in this weather.

Text.SourceString: I heard a really loud howl last night coming from your part of the island.
Text.LocalizedString: I heard a really loud howl last night coming from your part of the island.

Text.SourceString: I wonder if it was your pet or <NPCName>Luke’s</> dog, <NPCName>Taco</>.
Text.LocalizedString: I wonder if it was your pet or <NPCName>Luke’s</> dog, <NPCName>Taco</>.

Text.SourceString: We lost Mom in Fall, some years ago. It’s always the hardest season for <NPCName>Theo</> and me, but he won’t admit it, ’cause he’s always so good at hiding his emotions.
Text.LocalizedString: We lost Mom in Fall, some years ago. It’s always the hardest season for <NPCName>Theo</> and me, but he won’t admit it, ’cause he’s always so good at hiding his emotions.

Text.SourceString: I wish <NPCName>Theo</> wouldn’t hide his feelings and just let them out, ’cause if you strain something too long, it’ll eventually break. I don’t want my brother to break.
Text.LocalizedString: I wish <NPCName>Theo</> wouldn’t hide his feelings and just let them out, ’cause if you strain something too long, it’ll eventually break. I don’t want my brother to break.

Text.SourceString: I’m <Italic>never</> taking my hoodie off.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m <Italic>never</> taking my hoodie off.

Text.SourceString: Especially when it snows like this!
Text.LocalizedString: Especially when it snows like this!

Text.SourceString: Hot cocoa sounds so good right now.
Text.LocalizedString: Hot cocoa sounds so good right now.

Text.SourceString: I have some jewelry made from jade. If you want to find some, watch out for treasure chests.//Sometimes there’s jade in them.
Text.LocalizedString: I have some jewelry made from jade. If you want to find some, watch out for treasure chests.//Sometimes there’s jade in them.

Text.SourceString: No, I don’t think jade is natural in this area.
Text.LocalizedString: No, I don’t think jade is natural in this area.

Text.SourceString: I have some jewelry made from jade. If you want to find some, watch out for treasure chests.//Sometimes there’s jade in them.
Text.LocalizedString: I have some jewelry made from jade. If you want to find some, watch out for treasure chests.//Sometimes there’s jade in them.

Text.SourceString: No, I don’t think jade is natural in this area.
Text.LocalizedString: No, I don’t think jade is natural in this area.

Text.SourceString: I tried to tell my dad about a game concept I was developing, and I got a lecture about “real jobs” instead.
Text.LocalizedString: I tried to tell my dad about a game concept I was developing, and I got a lecture about “real jobs” instead.

Text.SourceString: Bummer.
Text.LocalizedString: Bummer.

Text.SourceString: I’m just going to relax and enjoy the rain for a bit.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m just going to relax and enjoy the rain for a bit.

Text.SourceString: I’ll just work later.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ll just work later.

Text.SourceString: One thing I like about this job is I can set my own hours.//I have the flexibility to do my own thing, like making games or playing them, which is cool.
Text.LocalizedString: One thing I like about this job is I can set my own hours.//I have the flexibility to do my own thing, like making games or playing them, which is cool.

Text.SourceString: I might just work tomorrow. The rain makes me feel a bit lazy.//<portrait=concerned>I don’t know. Maybe I’ll play games instead. I have plenty of games I haven’t played in my Vapor account .
Text.LocalizedString: I might just work tomorrow. The rain makes me feel a bit lazy.//<portrait=concerned>I don’t know. Maybe I’ll play games instead. I have plenty of games I haven’t played in my Vapor account .

Text.SourceString: One thing I like about this job is I can set my own hours.//I have the flexibility to do my own thing, like making games or playing them, which is cool.
Text.LocalizedString: One thing I like about this job is I can set my own hours.//I have the flexibility to do my own thing, like making games or playing them, which is cool.

Text.SourceString: The snow just keeps piling up.
Text.LocalizedString: The snow just keeps piling up.

Text.SourceString: Some of my bonsai are dropping leaves.
Text.LocalizedString: Some of my bonsai are dropping leaves.

Text.SourceString: Brrrr!
Text.LocalizedString: Brrrr!

Text.SourceString: I’m mostly here to support <NPCName>Theo</>.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m mostly here to support <NPCName>Theo</>.

Text.SourceString: Not usually a big fan of crowds.
Text.LocalizedString: Not usually a big fan of crowds.

Text.SourceString: Umm. Are you here to see me?
Text.LocalizedString: Umm. Are you here to see me?

Text.SourceString: I rarely get any visitors.
Text.LocalizedString: I rarely get any visitors.

Text.SourceString: *mumbling* It doesn’t work, and I don’t know why.
Text.LocalizedString: *mumbling* It doesn’t work, and I don’t know why.

Text.SourceString: *mumbling* It worked perfectly before.
Text.LocalizedString: *mumbling* It worked perfectly before.

Text.SourceString: I use an alias for game development to keep my hobby separate from my job.
Text.LocalizedString: I use an alias for game development to keep my hobby separate from my job.

Text.SourceString: Sorry, can’t tell you. You’re just going to have to find out on your own.//<portrait=normal>But I’ll give you one clue. You’ve been staring at it all along.
Text.LocalizedString: Sorry, can’t tell you. You’re just going to have to find out on your own.//<portrait=normal>But I’ll give you one clue. You’ve been staring at it all along.

Text.SourceString: I really have to focus on this right now.
Text.LocalizedString: I really have to focus on this right now.

Text.SourceString: It’s nice of you to visit.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s nice of you to visit.

Text.SourceString: I work in the kitchen sometimes instead of just in my room.//I heard it’s important to change things up.
Text.LocalizedString: I work in the kitchen sometimes instead of just in my room.//I heard it’s important to change things up.

Text.SourceString: I’m glad I took the advice.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m glad I took the advice.

Text.SourceString: They’re small, but bonsai require a lot of care.
Text.LocalizedString: They’re small, but bonsai require a lot of care.

Text.SourceString: Focusing on gardening helps me organize my thoughts.
Text.LocalizedString: Focusing on gardening helps me organize my thoughts.

Text.SourceString: Ouch!
Text.LocalizedString: Ouch!

Text.SourceString: Watch your step, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Watch your step, <PlayerName>$player</>.

Text.SourceString: Oops. Sorry!
Text.LocalizedString: Oops. Sorry!

Text.SourceString: Didn’t mean to step on your foot.
Text.LocalizedString: Didn’t mean to step on your foot.

Text.SourceString: My brother caught a legendary fish here one time.
Text.LocalizedString: My brother caught a legendary fish here one time.

Text.SourceString: A flowerhorn, I believe. The one with a huge forehead and kind of rounded body.
Text.LocalizedString: A flowerhorn, I believe. The one with a huge forehead and kind of rounded body.

Text.SourceString: Mom used to bring <NPCName>Theo</> and me here to do our homework on our way back from school.
Text.LocalizedString: Mom used to bring <NPCName>Theo</> and me here to do our homework on our way back from school.

Text.SourceString: This is a bit far from your cabin, isn’t it?
Text.LocalizedString: This is a bit far from your cabin, isn’t it?

Text.SourceString: Having a beach day, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Having a beach day, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: It’s the perfect weather for diving, wouldn’t you agree?
Text.LocalizedString: It’s the perfect weather for diving, wouldn’t you agree?

Text.SourceString: It’s crazy to think sometimes that <NPCName>Suki</> has a young girl.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s crazy to think sometimes that <NPCName>Suki</> has a young girl.

Text.SourceString: Maybe someday I could be a mom too.//Other than to my bonsai, that is.
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe someday I could be a mom too.//Other than to my bonsai, that is.

Text.SourceString: A nice hot bath...the quiet Winter night. That would be perfect.
Text.LocalizedString: A nice hot bath...the quiet Winter night. That would be perfect.

Text.SourceString: I know I’m not good at keeping in contact sometimes. I just get exhausted easily from socializing.//<portrait=normal>I feel like you get me, and I’m grateful for it.
Text.LocalizedString: I know I’m not good at keeping in contact sometimes. I just get exhausted easily from socializing.//<portrait=normal>I feel like you get me, and I’m grateful for it.

Text.SourceString: It’s nice to have friends.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s nice to have friends.

Text.SourceString: Hey you, farmer!//What’s up?
Text.LocalizedString: Hey you, farmer!//What’s up?

Text.SourceString: Too chummy? Ha! You’re right.//<portrait=blushing>It felt weird.
Text.LocalizedString: Too chummy? Ha! You’re right.//<portrait=blushing>It felt weird.

Text.SourceString: Sorry if I come across as cold and distant sometimes.
Text.LocalizedString: Sorry if I come across as cold and distant sometimes.

Text.SourceString: Strangers scare me. Especially the ones who are really friendly right away.//<portrait=annoyed>It makes me feel attacked, for some reason.
Text.LocalizedString: Strangers scare me. Especially the ones who are really friendly right away.//<portrait=annoyed>It makes me feel attacked, for some reason.

Text.SourceString: I went to the lake yesterday and dipped my feet in the water.
Text.LocalizedString: I went to the lake yesterday and dipped my feet in the water.

Text.SourceString: It was <Italic>very</> cold.
Text.LocalizedString: It was <Italic>very</> cold.

Text.SourceString: I’m getting used to seeing you around. I kind of like it.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m getting used to seeing you around. I kind of like it.

Text.SourceString: Oh darn, I wish I could hang out with you today. But I have a deadline at midnight, so I’m swamped.//<portrait=concerned>Don’t be mad, okay?
Text.LocalizedString: Oh darn, I wish I could hang out with you today. But I have a deadline at midnight, so I’m swamped.//<portrait=concerned>Don’t be mad, okay?

Text.SourceString: I’ve spotted a few colorful birds while out tending my bonsai.//There are so many of them on this island.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve spotted a few colorful birds while out tending my bonsai.//There are so many of them on this island.

Text.SourceString: As long as they don’t attack my plants, I’m okay with them.
Text.LocalizedString: As long as they don’t attack my plants, I’m okay with them.

Text.SourceString: Having a pet must be nice.
Text.LocalizedString: Having a pet must be nice.

Text.SourceString: I think I could be a pretty good fish mom.//They don’t require too much attention.
Text.LocalizedString: I think I could be a pretty good fish mom.//They don’t require too much attention.

Text.SourceString: I caught <NPCName>Dippa</> talking to my bonsai a few times.//It was always early in the morning too, like they were hiding it or something.
Text.LocalizedString: I caught <NPCName>Dippa</> talking to my bonsai a few times.//It was always early in the morning too, like they were hiding it or something.

Text.SourceString: Is that weird? I don’t want to bring it up with them, because it seems personal.//<portrait=normal>I don’t want to call them out like that, you know?
Text.LocalizedString: Is that weird? I don’t want to bring it up with them, because it seems personal.//<portrait=normal>I don’t want to call them out like that, you know?

Text.SourceString: It’s nice to see my coworkers and bosses every once in a while.//<portrait=concerned>But good Goddess, please not too often.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s nice to see my coworkers and bosses every once in a while.//<portrait=concerned>But good Goddess, please not too often.

Text.SourceString: Socializing isn’t my strongest skill.//<portrait=sad>I think if the company started having more mandatory in-person meetings, my coworkers might start hating me <Italic>fast</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Socializing isn’t my strongest skill.//<portrait=sad>I think if the company started having more mandatory in-person meetings, my coworkers might start hating me <Italic>fast</>.

Text.SourceString: I really like spending time with you.
Text.LocalizedString: I really like spending time with you.

Text.SourceString: Aww. Don’t worry about my work.//You can come over any time!
Text.LocalizedString: Aww. Don’t worry about my work.//You can come over any time!

Text.SourceString: I feel so much pressure sometimes when I hang out with my friends.//And the worst thing is it’s for no reason at all. I know, it’s weird.
Text.LocalizedString: I feel so much pressure sometimes when I hang out with my friends.//And the worst thing is it’s for no reason at all. I know, it’s weird.

Text.SourceString: I know deep down that none of my friends would judge me.//But I still have this irrational fear I’ll mess up if I open my mouth.
Text.LocalizedString: I know deep down that none of my friends would judge me.//But I still have this irrational fear I’ll mess up if I open my mouth.

Text.SourceString: Every time I talk, I feel like I’m about to embarrass myself, and everyone will make fun of what I say.
Text.LocalizedString: Every time I talk, I feel like I’m about to embarrass myself, and everyone will make fun of what I say.

Text.SourceString: I just know it in my bones.
Text.LocalizedString: I just know it in my bones.

Text.SourceString: As much as I want to be 100 percent transparent with my family, some things, umm… Some things I just can’t talk to Dad about as freely as I can with you.
Text.LocalizedString: As much as I want to be 100 percent transparent with my family, some things, umm… Some things I just can’t talk to Dad about as freely as I can with you.

Text.SourceString: When you first got here, I didn’t want to talk to you too much. I figured you must get a lot of attention already, and I empathized with you.//If it were me, I’d want some space.
Text.LocalizedString: When you first got here, I didn’t want to talk to you too much. I figured you must get a lot of attention already, and I empathized with you.//If it were me, I’d want some space.

Text.SourceString: I also don’t like strangers. Heh heh. You’re right!//<portrait=happy>You’re funny.
Text.LocalizedString: I also don’t like strangers. Heh heh. You’re right!//<portrait=happy>You’re funny.

Text.SourceString: It takes time, but I think my meditation is finally working.//The first few times I tried meditating, I kept falling asleep.
Text.LocalizedString: It takes time, but I think my meditation is finally working.//The first few times I tried meditating, I kept falling asleep.

Text.SourceString: I asked <NpcName>Leah</> about it, and she told me to keep going. Pretty normal to fall asleep, she said.//<portrait=happy>Glad I did.
Text.LocalizedString: I asked <NpcName>Leah</> about it, and she told me to keep going. Pretty normal to fall asleep, she said.//<portrait=happy>Glad I did.

Text.SourceString: The only downside of my job that I can think of is it’s hard to keep a regular schedule if you work from home.
Text.LocalizedString: The only downside of my job that I can think of is it’s hard to keep a regular schedule if you work from home.

Text.SourceString: I mean, if you work remotely in front of a computer, like me.//<portrait=happy>I guess it isn’t hard to keep a schedule as a farmer, huh?
Text.LocalizedString: I mean, if you work remotely in front of a computer, like me.//<portrait=happy>I guess it isn’t hard to keep a schedule as a farmer, huh?

Text.SourceString: I know it’s a lot of work and energy, but I think meditation helps my nerves.
Text.LocalizedString: I know it’s a lot of work and energy, but I think meditation helps my nerves.

Text.SourceString: I do still feel nervous every now and then, but I can tell it’s helping.
Text.LocalizedString: I do still feel nervous every now and then, but I can tell it’s helping.

Text.SourceString: Because of the nature of my job – security – I can’t talk about it much, which is a bummer because it’s one of the only things I know enough about to discuss.//<portrait=happy>Another thing I can confidently talk about is my bonsai.
Text.LocalizedString: Because of the nature of my job – security – I can’t talk about it much, which is a bummer because it’s one of the only things I know enough about to discuss.//<portrait=happy>Another thing I can confidently talk about is my bonsai.

Text.SourceString: I name them, you know.//One of them is named <NPCName>Theodore</>. Can you guess which one?
Text.LocalizedString: I name them, you know.//One of them is named <NPCName>Theodore</>. Can you guess which one?

Text.SourceString: Mom would’ve loved you. You’re nice and easy to talk to.
Text.LocalizedString: Mom would’ve loved you. You’re nice and easy to talk to.

Text.SourceString: And I think you would’ve liked Mom too.//<portrait=normal>She wasn’t stern like Dad.
Text.LocalizedString: And I think you would’ve liked Mom too.//<portrait=normal>She wasn’t stern like Dad.

Text.SourceString: Taking care of my bonsai is the one thing that keeps me on a schedule.
Text.LocalizedString: Taking care of my bonsai is the one thing that keeps me on a schedule.

Text.SourceString: I know myself enough to know that routine eases my mind. So in a way, my bonsai are my Zen teachers.
Text.LocalizedString: I know myself enough to know that routine eases my mind. So in a way, my bonsai are my Zen teachers.

Text.SourceString: Being here feels like nothing has changed in my family.//<portrait=sad>It feels like Mom is just out grocery shopping or diving.
Text.LocalizedString: Being here feels like nothing has changed in my family.//<portrait=sad>It feels like Mom is just out grocery shopping or diving.

Text.SourceString: And sometimes, I pretend that maybe she is.
Text.LocalizedString: And sometimes, I pretend that maybe she is.

Text.SourceString: I hope I’m not prying here.//Are you into anyone on this island?
Text.LocalizedString: I hope I’m not prying here.//Are you into anyone on this island?

Text.SourceString: That’s awesome! I’m glad things are working out for you here.
Text.LocalizedString: That’s awesome! I’m glad things are working out for you here.

Special.SourceString: Yes, but I can’t say. We aren’t official yet.
Special.LocalizedString: Yes, but I can’t say. We aren’t official yet.

Text.SourceString: I think you’re really cute.
Text.LocalizedString: I think you’re really cute.

Special.SourceString: Yes. I’m looking right at her.
Special.LocalizedString: Yes. I’m looking right at her.

Text.SourceString: I get that.//Oh well.
Text.LocalizedString: I get that.//Oh well.

Special.SourceString: No. My ex still has my heart.
Special.LocalizedString: No. My ex still has my heart.

Text.SourceString: I like having you over.//It’s less empty with you here.
Text.LocalizedString: I like having you over.//It’s less empty with you here.

Text.SourceString: Though I prefer it dead and empty to having other people visit.//They’re a distraction, and not the good kind.
Text.LocalizedString: Though I prefer it dead and empty to having other people visit.//They’re a distraction, and not the good kind.

Text.SourceString: I’ve thought about moving to Pokyo.//It would cost me a fortune to move my bonsai if I ever went there for work.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve thought about moving to Pokyo.//It would cost me a fortune to move my bonsai if I ever went there for work.

Text.SourceString: What? No. I can’t leave my bonsai here. They’re my babies.
Text.LocalizedString: What? No. I can’t leave my bonsai here. They’re my babies.

Text.SourceString: Hmm. I’m in the mood to make a big batch of lodeh.
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm. I’m in the mood to make a big batch of lodeh.

Text.SourceString: Small problem, though. I don’t have any eggplant.
Text.LocalizedString: Small problem, though. I don’t have any eggplant.

Text.SourceString: I’m running out of RAM already. *sighs*
Text.LocalizedString: I’m running out of RAM already. *sighs*

Text.SourceString: It’s so expensive, too.//<portrait=normal>Good thing the company covers the cost.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s so expensive, too.//<portrait=normal>Good thing the company covers the cost.

Text.SourceString: <Italic>Oh no! It crashed!</> //<Italic>Oh no, no, no, no!</>
Text.LocalizedString: <Italic>Oh no! It crashed!</> //<Italic>Oh no, no, no, no!</>

Text.SourceString: I’m beyond sad right now.//Compiling takes <Italic>ages</>, and now all my hard work today is gone.//<portrait=concerned>I need to go for a walk.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m beyond sad right now.//Compiling takes <Italic>ages</>, and now all my hard work today is gone.//<portrait=concerned>I need to go for a walk.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Theo</> is rarely home.//It’s easier to work when he’s out. Less singing going on in the house.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Theo</> is rarely home.//It’s easier to work when he’s out. Less singing going on in the house.

Text.SourceString: I think I’ll skip this year’s team-bonding trip. It’s in the first week of Fall.//I really don’t want to go to cider-making camp.
Text.LocalizedString: I think I’ll skip this year’s team-bonding trip. It’s in the first week of Fall.//I really don’t want to go to cider-making camp.

Text.SourceString: Good thing my manager never requires us to attend.
Text.LocalizedString: Good thing my manager never requires us to attend.

Text.SourceString: It’s nice here.//The sun is warm today.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s nice here.//The sun is warm today.

Text.SourceString: Not too many people like this part of the beach.//<portrait=happy>It’s perfect for me.
Text.LocalizedString: Not too many people like this part of the beach.//<portrait=happy>It’s perfect for me.

Text.SourceString: I think I’m going to spend the day here, enjoying the weather.//Where are you heading, <PlayerName>$Player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: I think I’m going to spend the day here, enjoying the weather.//Where are you heading, <PlayerName>$Player</>?

Text.SourceString: Are you planting any lilies on your farm?//It’s the season, isn’t it?
Text.LocalizedString: Are you planting any lilies on your farm?//It’s the season, isn’t it?

Text.SourceString: I only know because my mom told me Summer is lily season.//<portrait=blushing>They were in her wedding bouquet.
Text.LocalizedString: I only know because my mom told me Summer is lily season.//<portrait=blushing>They were in her wedding bouquet.

Text.SourceString: Mom is in a better place.//<portrait=normal>That thought keeps me sane.
Text.LocalizedString: Mom is in a better place.//<portrait=normal>That thought keeps me sane.

Text.SourceString: I’m not afraid of death.//Because when my time comes, I know Mom will be there with me.//<portrait=normal>She won’t let me be alone.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not afraid of death.//Because when my time comes, I know Mom will be there with me.//<portrait=normal>She won’t let me be alone.

Text.SourceString: We still have some of Mom’s dresses.//I keep some in my closet, and the rest are in Dad’s room.
Text.LocalizedString: We still have some of Mom’s dresses.//I keep some in my closet, and the rest are in Dad’s room.

Text.SourceString: When I get married someday, I’ll wear Mom’s wedding dress.//It’s my size.
Text.LocalizedString: When I get married someday, I’ll wear Mom’s wedding dress.//It’s my size.

Text.SourceString: I might modify it a bit to make it more <Italic>me</>.
Text.LocalizedString: I might modify it a bit to make it more <Italic>me</>.

Text.SourceString: You’re making me a bit nervous. I can feel my heart about to jump out of my shirt.
Text.LocalizedString: You’re making me a bit nervous. I can feel my heart about to jump out of my shirt.

Text.SourceString: Do you like this color on me?//<portrait=blushing>Thank you. You’re so sweet!
Text.LocalizedString: Do you like this color on me?//<portrait=blushing>Thank you. You’re so sweet!

Text.SourceString: Wanna watch something and chill in my room?
Text.LocalizedString: Wanna watch something and chill in my room?

Text.SourceString: Give me a second. Let me save my work real quick.
Text.LocalizedString: Give me a second. Let me save my work real quick.

Text.SourceString: Have you eaten? If not, I can make you something quick.//I think we have onigiri in the fridge.
Text.LocalizedString: Have you eaten? If not, I can make you something quick.//I think we have onigiri in the fridge.

Text.SourceString: Would you like some hot tea, <PlayerName>$Player</>?//I’m afraid we only have hot tea. And an abundance of milk.
